duct-reviews">Product Reviews</a><br><a href="/magazine/five-questions-david-eicher">5 Questions with David Eicher</a></div></div></div></div><div class="navhover newsSwatch"><div class="inner"><div class="column1"><div class="previewImage"><a href="/news/2019/04/the-event-horizon-telescope-may-soon-release-first-ever-black-hole-image"><img src="/-/media/Images/News and Observing/News/2019/04/blackhole.png?mw=300" alt="blackhole" width="300" height="290" /></a></div><div><a href="/news/2019/04/the-event-horizon-telescope-may-soon-release-first-ever-black-hole-image">The Event Horizon Telescope may soon release first-ever black hole image</a></div></div><div class="column2"><h3>RECENT HEADLINES</h3><ul><li><a href="/news/2019/04/mercury-venus-and-neptune-rise-with-the-crescent-moon-tomorrow-morning">Mercury, Venus, and Neptune rise with the crescent Moon tomorrow morning</a></li><li><a href="/news/2019/04/astronomers-finally-confirm-methane-on-mars">Astronomers finally confirm methane on Mars</a></li><li><a href="/observing/sky-this-week/2019/03/the-sky-this-week-from-march-29-to-april-7">The Sky This Week from March 29 to April 7</a></li><li><a href="/news/2019/03/ghostly-galaxy-without-dark-matter-confirmed">Second ghostly galaxy without dark matter discovered, first confirmed</a></li><li><a href="/news/2019/03/the-case-for-trident-nasas-shrinking-window-for-a-mission-to-triton">The case for Trident: NASAâs shrinking window for a mission to Triton</a></li><li><a href="/news/2019/03/ligo-is-searching-for-gravitational-waves-again">LIGO is searching for gravitational waves again, and here's what scientists hope to learn</a></li><li><a href="/news/2019/03/saturns-small-moons-formed-from-the-dust-of-its-rings">Saturn's small moons formed from the dust of its rings</a></li></ul></div><div class="column3"><h3>TOPICS</h3><div class="left"><ul><li><a href="/tags/solar-system">solar system</a></li><li><a href="/tags/galaxies">galaxies</a></li><li><a href="/tags/stars">sta